## 2. Opcode/Packet Parsing Architecture

### Opcode Definitions
**`/home/openclaw/code/tuicraft/src/wow/protocol/opcodes.ts`**

All opcodes live in a single `GameOpcode` const object. It contains ~350+ opcodes organized by area (auth, chat, group, guild, movement, spells, combat, etc.). Also defines enums for `ChatType`, `Language`, `PartyResult`, `PartyOperation`, `GroupUpdateFlag`, `ChannelNotify`, `ChallengeResult`, and `AuthOpcode`.

### Packet Reader/Writer
**`/home/openclaw/code/tuicraft/src/wow/protocol/packet.ts`**

Two classes provide the low-level binary read/write layer:

```typescript
export class PacketReader {
  constructor(data: Uint8Array, offset = 0)
  uint8(): number
  uint16LE(): number
  uint32LE(): number
  uint64LE(): bigint
  floatLE(): number
  bytes(n: number): Uint8Array
  cString(): string
  skip(n: number)
  packedGuid(): { low: number; high: number }
  get remaining(): number
  get offset(): number
}

export class PacketWriter {
  constructor(initialSize = 64)
  uint8(v: number)
  uint16LE(v: number)
  uint32LE(v: number)
  uint64LE(v: bigint)
  floatLE(v: number)
  rawBytes(data: Uint8Array)
  cString(s: string)
  finish(): Uint8Array
  get offset(): number
}
```

### World Packet Framing
**`/home/openclaw/code/tuicraft/src/wow/protocol/world.ts`**

Handles the world server wire protocol:

- `buildOutgoingPacket(opcode, body, arc4?)` -- creates a 6-byte header (2 size big-endian + 4 opcode little-endian), optionally ARC4-encrypts the header, then appends the body.
- `decryptIncomingHeader(header, arc4?)` -- decrypts a 4-byte header and extracts `{ size, opcode }` (2 size big-endian + 2 opcode little-endian).
- `AccumulatorBuffer` -- byte accumulator for reassembling TCP fragments.
- `OpcodeDispatch` -- the central handler dispatch system (see section 5).

