## 3. SMSG Handler Registration Pattern

**`/home/openclaw/code/tuicraft/src/wow/protocol/world.ts`** -- `OpcodeDispatch` class:

```typescript
export class OpcodeDispatch {
  on(opcode: number, handler: (reader: PacketReader) => void)  // register permanent handler
  expect(opcode: number, timeoutMs = 10_000): Promise<PacketReader>  // one-shot await
  handle(opcode: number, reader: PacketReader)  // dispatch incoming packet
  has(opcode: number): boolean  // check if handler registered
}
```

The `handle()` method checks `expects` first (one-shot promise resolvers used during login handshake), then falls back to permanent `handlers`.

### Handler Registration in client.ts

In **`/home/openclaw/code/tuicraft/src/wow/client.ts`**, the `worldSession()` function registers all SMSG handlers on lines 891-951. The pattern is:

```typescript
conn.dispatch.on(GameOpcode.SMSG_MESSAGE_CHAT, (r) => handleChatMessage(conn, r));
conn.dispatch.on(GameOpcode.SMSG_GROUP_INVITE, (r) => handleGroupInviteReceived(conn, r));
conn.dispatch.on(GameOpcode.SMSG_UPDATE_OBJECT, (r) => handleUpdateObject(conn, r));
// ... etc
