## 5. Data Stores

### EntityStore
**`/home/openclaw/code/tuicraft/src/wow/entity-store.ts`**

The central entity tracking system. Stores all entities (players, NPCs, game objects) that are visible to the client.

```typescript
export class EntityStore {
  create(guid: bigint, objectType: ObjectType, fields: EntityFields): void
  update(guid: bigint, fields: Record<string, unknown>): void
  destroy(guid: bigint): void
  clear(): void
  get(guid: bigint): Entity | undefined
  getByType(type: ObjectType): Entity[]
  all(): Entity[]
  setName(guid: bigint, name: string): void
  setPosition(guid: bigint, pos: Position): void
  onEvent(cb: (event: EntityEvent) => void): void
}
```

Entity types:
- `BaseEntity` -- `{ guid, objectType, entry, scale, position, rawFields, name }`
- `UnitEntity extends BaseEntity` -- adds `health, maxHealth, level, factionTemplate, displayId, npcFlags, unitFlags, target, race, class_, gender, power[], maxPower[]`
- `GameObjectEntity extends BaseEntity` -- adds `displayId, flags, gameObjectType, bytes1`
- `Entity = UnitEntity | GameObjectEntity | BaseEntity`

Events: `EntityEvent = { type: "appear", entity } | { type: "disappear", guid, name } | { type: "update", entity, changed }`

Internally uses `Map<bigint, Entity>` and `Map<number, Set<bigint>>` (by-type index).

