### 3. SMSG_FRIEND_STATUS (0x0068) -- Friend Status Update

This packet is sent in response to add/remove friend operations and also broadcast when a friend comes online/offline. The binary layout has **conditional fields** depending on the `result` value, but the wowm spec for 3.3.5 does not capture these conditionals -- the AzerothCore source is the authoritative reference.

**Base layout (always present):**

| Offset | Type | Field |
|---|---|---|
| 0 | u8 | result (FriendResult enum) |
| 1 | u64 (Guid) | guid |

**Conditional fields based on result:**

| Result Value | Additional Fields |
|---|---|
| ADDED_OFFLINE (0x07) or ADDED_ONLINE (0x06) | + CString note |
| ADDED_ONLINE (0x06) or ONLINE (0x02) | + u8 status + u32 area + u32 level + u32 class |

From `/home/openclaw/code/wow_messages/wow_message_parser/wowm/world/social/smsg_friend_status.wowm` (3.3.5 version -- incomplete, only base fields):
```
