### How Online Status and Area/Zone Info Is Populated

From `/home/openclaw/code/azerothcore-wotlk-playerbots/src/server/game/Entities/Player/SocialMgr.cpp` lines 212-248:
```cpp
void SocialMgr::GetFriendInfo(Player* player, ObjectGuid const& friendGUID, FriendInfo& friendInfo)
{
    if (!player)
        return;

    friendInfo.Status = FRIEND_STATUS_OFFLINE;
    friendInfo.Area = 0;
    friendInfo.Level = 0;
    friendInfo.Class = 0;

    Player* pFriend = ObjectAccessor::FindConnectedPlayer(friendGUID);
    if (!pFriend || pFriend->GetSession()->IsGMAccount())
        return;

    // ... visibility checks ...

    if (/* visible */)
    {
        friendInfo.Status = FRIEND_STATUS_ONLINE;
        if (pFriend->isAFK())
            friendInfo.Status = FRIEND_STATUS_AFK;
        if (pFriend->isDND())
            friendInfo.Status = FRIEND_STATUS_DND;
        friendInfo.Area = pFriend->GetZoneId();
        friendInfo.Level = pFriend->GetLevel();
        friendInfo.Class = pFriend->getClass();
    }
}
```

Key points:
- `Area` is the **zone ID** (from `GetZoneId()`), not the area ID.
- GM accounts are always shown as offline to non-GMs.
- Cross-faction friend visibility is controlled by server config (`CONFIG_ALLOW_TWO_SIDE_WHO_LIST`).
- AFK overrides ONLINE, then DND overrides both (last-write-wins, so DND takes priority if both are set).
- Level and Class are written as `uint32` in the packet despite being `uint8` in the struct.

---

### Broadcast Behavior

When a friend logs in or out, `SendFriendStatus` is called with `broadcast = true`, which calls `BroadcastToFriendListers` (SocialMgr.cpp lines 294-317). This iterates over ALL players' social maps to find who has the logging-in/out player as a friend, and sends them an SMSG_FRIEND_STATUS with result FRIEND_ONLINE (0x02) or FRIEND_OFFLINE (0x03).

