### 2. SMSG_CONTACT_LIST (0x0067) -- Contact List Response

This is the most complex packet. It contains a list of all contacts matching the requested flags, with conditional online-status fields for friends.

**Binary layout:**

| Offset | Type | Field | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| 0 | u32 | list_mask | RelationType flags echoed back from request |
| 4 | u32 | amount_of_relations | Number of contacts in the list |
| 8+ | Relation[] | relations | Repeated `amount_of_relations` times (variable size) |

**Each Relation entry:**

| Offset | Type | Field | Condition | Description |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| +0 | u64 (Guid) | guid | always | Player GUID |
| +8 | u32 | relation_mask | always | RelationType flags for this contact |
| +12 | CString | note | always | Null-terminated note string |
| +N | u8 | status | only if `relation_mask & FRIEND` | FriendStatus enum |
| +N+1 | u32 | area | only if `relation_mask & FRIEND` AND `status != OFFLINE` | Zone/area ID |
| +N+5 | u32 | level | only if `relation_mask & FRIEND` AND `status != OFFLINE` | Player level |
| +N+9 | u32 | class | only if `relation_mask & FRIEND` AND `status != OFFLINE` | Player class |

From `/home/openclaw/code/wow_messages/wow_message_parser/wowm/world/social/smsg_contact_list.wowm`:
```
flag RelationType : u32 {
    NONE = 0x00;
    FRIEND = 0x01;
    IGNORED = 0x02;
    MUTED = 0x04;
    RECRUITAFRIEND = 0x08;
} {
    versions = "2.4.3 3";
}

enum FriendStatus : u8 {
    OFFLINE = 0;
    ONLINE = 1;
    AFK = 2;
    UNKNOWN3 = 3;
    DND = 4;
} {
     versions = "2.4.3 3";
 }

struct Relation {
    Guid guid;
    RelationType relation_mask;
    CString note;
    if (relation_mask & FRIEND) {
        FriendStatus status;
        if (status == ONLINE)
        {
            Area area;
            Level32 level;
            (u32)Class class;
        }
    }
} {
      paste_versions = "2.4.3 3.3.5";
}

smsg SMSG_CONTACT_LIST = 0x0067 {
    /// Indicates which kinds of relations are being sent in this list
    RelationType list_mask;
    u32 amount_of_relations;
    Relation[amount_of_relations] relations;
} {
     paste_versions = "2.4.3 3.3.5";
}
```

**IMPORTANT NOTE about the wowm spec vs AzerothCore:** The wowm spec says `if (status == ONLINE)` for the conditional area/level/class block, but the AzerothCore implementation uses `if (friendInfo.Status)` -- i.e., it checks for any non-zero status. This means AFK (2) and DND (4) players also include the area/level/class fields. The AzerothCore implementation is the authoritative behavior for 3.3.5a.

From `/home/openclaw/code/azerothcore-wotlk-playerbots/src/server/game/Entities/Player/SocialMgr.cpp` lines 124-177 (the actual packet construction):
```cpp
void PlayerSocial::SendSocialList(Player* player, uint32 flags)
{
    if (!player)
        return;

    uint32 friendsCount = 0;
    uint32 ignoredCount = 0;
    uint32 totalCount = 0;

    WorldPacket data(SMSG_CONTACT_LIST, (4 + 4 + m_playerSocialMap.size() * 25)); // just can guess size
    data << uint32(flags);                                                        // 0x1 = Friendlist update. 0x2 = Ignorelist update. 0x4 = Mutelist update.
    std::size_t countPos = data.wpos();
    data << uint32(0);                                                           // contacts count placeholder

    for (auto& itr : m_playerSocialMap)
    {
        FriendInfo& friendInfo = itr.second;
        uint8 contactFlags = friendInfo.Flags;
        if (!(contactFlags & flags))
            continue;

        // Check client limit for friends list
        if (contactFlags & SOCIAL_FLAG_FRIEND)
            if (++friendsCount > SOCIALMGR_FRIEND_LIMIT)
                continue;

        // Check client limit for ignore list
        if (contactFlags & SOCIAL_FLAG_IGNORED)
            if (++ignoredCount > SOCIALMGR_IGNORE_LIMIT)
                continue;

        ++totalCount;

        sSocialMgr->GetFriendInfo(player, itr.first, friendInfo);

        data << itr.first;                                    // player guid
        data << uint32(contactFlags);                         // player flag (0x1 = Friend, 0x2 = Ignored, 0x4 = Muted)
        data << friendInfo.Note;                              // string note
        if (contactFlags & SOCIAL_FLAG_FRIEND)                // if IsFriend()
        {
            data << uint8(friendInfo.Status);                 // online/offline/etc?
            if (friendInfo.Status)                            // if online
            {
                data << uint32(friendInfo.Area);              // player area
                data << uint32(friendInfo.Level);             // player level
                data << uint32(friendInfo.Class);             // player class
            }
        }
    }

    data.put<uint32>(countPos, totalCount);
    player->SendDirectMessage(&data);
}
```

Key observation: The check is `if (friendInfo.Status)` (any non-zero value), NOT `if (status == ONLINE)`. So ONLINE (1), AFK (2), and DND (4) all include area/level/class. Only OFFLINE (0) omits them.

