You are implementing Task 4: FriendStore class

## Task Description

Create `src/wow/friend-store.ts` and `src/wow/friend-store.test.ts`.

### Types

```typescript
export type FriendEntry = {
  guid: bigint;
  name: string;
  note: string;
  status: number;
  area: number;
  level: number;
  playerClass: number;
};

export type FriendEvent =
  | { type: "friend-list"; friends: FriendEntry[] }
  | { type: "friend-online"; friend: FriendEntry }
  | { type: "friend-offline"; guid: bigint; name: string }
  | { type: "friend-added"; friend: FriendEntry }
  | { type: "friend-removed"; guid: bigint; name: string }
  | { type: "friend-error"; result: number; name: string };
```

### FriendStore Class

```typescript
export class FriendStore {
  private friends = new Map<bigint, FriendEntry>();
  private listener?: (event: FriendEvent) => void;

  onEvent(cb): void — set listener
  set(entries: FriendEntry[]): void — clear + bulk replace, fire "friend-list" event
  add(entry: FriendEntry): void — insert single entry, fire "friend-added"
  update(guid, fields): void — modify existing entry. If status becomes 0, fire "friend-offline". If non-zero, fire "friend-online". Ignore unknown GUIDs.
  remove(guid): void — delete entry, fire "friend-removed". Ignore unknown GUIDs.
  setName(guid, name): void — update name on matching entry (no event)
  findByName(name): FriendEntry | undefined — case-insensitive name lookup
  all(): FriendEntry[] — return sorted by name
}
```

Key behaviors:
- `set()` clears previous entries before inserting new ones
- `update()` only accepts `Partial<Pick<FriendEntry, "status" | "area" | "level" | "playerClass">>`
- `all()` returns sorted by name (localeCompare)
- `findByName()` is case-insensitive
- Entries are stored as copies (spread on insert)

## Context

Follow the same class pattern as `src/wow/entity-store.ts` (Map-based storage + listener callback). This is a WoW 3.3.5a client. The project uses Bun, strict TypeScript, no comments.

## Tests to Write

- `set()` replaces all entries and fires friend-list event
- `set()` clears previous entries
- `update()` modifies existing entry and fires friend-online event (when status > 0)
- `update()` to offline fires friend-offline event (when status === 0)
- `update()` ignores unknown guid
- `add()` inserts new entry and fires friend-added event
- `remove()` deletes entry and fires friend-removed event
- `remove()` ignores unknown guid
- `setName()` updates name on matching entry
- `findByName()` returns entry by case-insensitive name
- `findByName()` returns undefined for unknown name
- `all()` returns sorted by name

## Your Job

1. Write tests first
2. Implement the class
3. Run `mise test src/wow/friend-store.test.ts` — all must pass
4. Commit with: `feat: Add FriendStore for friend list state`

